# IntelliCredit AI вҖ” Complete Setup Guide

> Everything YOU need to do, step by step, to get the full system running.

---

## What's Built vs What YOU Need To Do

| Layer | Built by me (code done вң…) | YOU need to do рҹ”§ |
|-------|---------------------------|-------------------|
| **Backend (FastAPI)** | All 7 API routers, 5 services, 4 agents | Install Python packages, start server |
| **Frontend (Next.js)** | 5 pages, Navbar, API client | Already installed (`npm install` done) |
| **Supabase (Database)** | Schema SQL file written | Create free project + run SQL |
| **Redis (Task Queue)** | Celery configured | Start Redis container |
| **Neo4j (Graph DB)** | Graph agent code done | Start Neo4j container (optional) |
| **ChromaDB (Vectors)** | Vector store code done | Installs automatically with pip |
| **Ollama (Local LLM)** | LLM service code done | Install Ollama + pull model (optional) |
| **ML Model (XGBoost)** | Training script done | Run training script once |
| **Docker** | Compose + Dockerfiles done | Run `docker compose up` |

---

## Step-by-Step Setup

### Step 1: Install Backend Python Packages

```powershell
cd m:\intelli-credit-ai-1\backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

> [!WARNING]
> This installs ~30 packages including FastAPI, XGBoost, PyMuPDF, etc.
> If any fail (like PyTorch), that's OK вҖ” the system works without them.
> The critical ones are: `fastapi`, `uvicorn`, `python-dotenv`, [supabase](file:///m:/intelli-credit-ai-1/backend/app/database.py#10-23), [openpyxl](file:///m:/intelli-credit-ai-1/backend/app/services/document_processor.py#39-46)

---

### Step 2: Set Up Supabase (FREE Database)

This is the **most important step** вҖ” without it, data won't persist.

1. Go to **[supabase.com](https://supabase.com)** вҶ’ Sign up (free)
2. Click **"New Project"** вҶ’ Name it `intellicredit` вҶ’ Set a DB password вҶ’ Create
3. Wait ~2 min for it to provision
4. Go to **SQL Editor** (left sidebar) вҶ’ Click **"New Query"**
5. Open this file and copy ALL its contents:

   ```
   m:\intelli-credit-ai-1\backend\supabase_schema.sql
   ```

6. Paste into SQL Editor вҶ’ Click **"Run"** вҶ’ Should say "Success"
7. Go to **Settings вҶ’ API** (left sidebar under gear icon)
8. Copy these 2 values:
   - **Project URL** (looks like `https://abcxyz.supabase.co`)
   - **anon public key** (long string starting with `eyJ...`)

9. Edit the backend [.env](file:///m:/intelli-credit-ai-1/backend/.env) file:

   ```powershell
   notepad m:\intelli-credit-ai-1\backend\.env
   ```

   Replace the placeholder values:
   ```
   SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-ID.supabase.co
   SUPABASE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.YOUR_KEY_HERE
   ```

   Save and close.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Without this step, the backend runs in "demo mode" вҖ” analysis works but nothing saves to DB.

---

### Step 3: Start Redis (Required for Celery task queue)

```powershell
docker run -d -p 6379:6379 --name intellicredit_redis redis:7-alpine
```

> [!NOTE]
> If you get "name already in use", run: `docker start intellicredit_redis`

---

### Step 4: Start Neo4j (OPTIONAL вҖ” for director graph risk)

```powershell
docker run -d -p 7474:7474 -p 7687:7687 --name intellicredit_neo4j -e NEO4J_AUTH=neo4j/password neo4j:5-community
```

- Web UI: **http://localhost:7474** (login: neo4j / password)
- Skip this if you don't need director cross-default risk detection

---

### Step 5: Train the ML Model (One time)

```powershell
cd m:\intelli-credit-ai-1
pip install xgboost scikit-learn
python ml\train_model.py
```

Expected output:
```
вң… Model trained successfully!
   AUC-ROC: 0.99xx
рҹ’ҫ Model saved to models/credit_risk_xgb.pkl
```

> [!NOTE]
> If you skip this, the system uses a heuristic fallback formula instead of XGBoost. It still works, just less accurate.

---

### Step 6: Install Ollama (OPTIONAL вҖ” for AI-enhanced CAM reports)

1. Download from **[ollama.com](https://ollama.com)** вҶ’ Install
2. Pull a model:
   ```powershell
   ollama pull llama3
   ```
3. Ollama runs automatically in background on port 11434

> [!NOTE]
> If you skip this, CAM reports use template text instead of AI-generated paragraphs. Still fully functional.

---

### Step 7: Start the Backend

```powershell
cd m:\intelli-credit-ai-1\backend
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```

Open **http://localhost:8000/docs** вҶ’ You should see Swagger UI with all 7 API groups.

---

### Step 8: Start the Frontend

Open a **new terminal**:

```powershell
cd m:\intelli-credit-ai-1\frontend
npm run dev
```

Open **http://localhost:3000** вҶ’ You should see the IntelliCredit AI home page.

---

### Step 9: Load Demo Data (OPTIONAL вҖ” skip if uploading real documents)

Open a **new terminal**:

```powershell
cd m:\intelli-credit-ai-1\backend
python ..\demo_data.py
```

This creates 3 companies with pre-computed analysis. View them at **http://localhost:3000/dashboard**.

---

### Step 10: Test the Full Pipeline

1. Open **http://localhost:3000/upload**
2. Enter: Company Name = `Test Company`, Industry = `Manufacturing`
3. Upload the sample file: `m:\intelli-credit-ai-1\sample_data\ABC_Steel_Annual_Report_2024.txt`
4. Watch the 4-step progress bar
5. View the Analysis page (charts, risk score)
6. View the CAM Report (6-section memo)

---

## Testing with Postman

Base URL: `http://localhost:8000`

| # | Method | URL | Body/Params |
|---|--------|-----|-------------|
| 1 | `POST` | `/api/documents/upload` | Form-data: [file](file:///m:/intelli-credit-ai-1/backend/Dockerfile) = PDF/TXT, `company_name` = "Test Co", [industry](file:///m:/intelli-credit-ai-1/backend/app/services/llm_service.py#103-113) = "Steel" |
| 2 | `GET` | `/api/companies/` | вҖ” |
| 3 | `POST` | `/api/risk/analyze` | JSON: `{"company_id": "ID_FROM_STEP_1", "industry": "Steel"}` |
| 4 | `POST` | `/api/research/run` | JSON: `{"company_id": "ID", "company_name": "Test Co", "industry": "Steel"}` |
| 5 | `POST` | `/api/cam/generate` | JSON: `{"company_id": "ID", "requested_loan_amount": 100000000}` |
| 6 | `GET` | `/api/cam/full/{company_id}` | вҖ” (returns everything) |
| 7 | `POST` | `/api/graph/risk-check` | JSON: `{"company_name": "Test Co"}` |
| 8 | `GET` | `/api/graph/status` | вҖ” (checks Neo4j connection) |
| 9 | `GET` | `/health` | вҖ” (backend health check) |

> [!TIP]
> Open **http://localhost:8000/docs** вҖ” FastAPI auto-generates an interactive API tester. You can test every endpoint without Postman!

---

## Docker Compose (Alternative вҖ” runs EVERYTHING in one command)

Instead of Steps 3-8, you can run everything via Docker:

```powershell
cd m:\intelli-credit-ai-1

# First, make sure .env is configured (Step 2 above)
docker compose up --build
```

This starts: Backend (:8000), Frontend (:3000), Redis (:6379), Neo4j (:7474/:7687), Celery Worker, Flower (:5555)

> [!CAUTION]
> Docker build takes 5-10 min the first time (downloads Python packages + Node modules).
> If Neo4j image pull fails due to network, comment it out in [docker-compose.yml](file:///m:/intelli-credit-ai-1/docker-compose.yml) вҖ” it's optional.

---

